A 32-year-old banker, Ifeanyi Otuesieme, on Monday appeared at a Tinubu Magistrates’ Court in Lagos for allegedly stealing N230,000 from his employer. Otuesieme is facing a charge of stealing to which he pleaded not guilty. Prosecuting Inspector Ajaga Agboko told the court that the defendant committed the offence last December at a bank on Victoria Island, Lagos. He alleged that the defendant, whose job description was to compute commissions paid to the bank’s direct sales agents, inflated the commissions by N230,000. Agboko said the offence contravened Section 287 (7) of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. Magistrate Mr. T. A. Anjorin-Ajose granted the defendant N200,000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. He adjourned the case till January 15.